definition: to fill/to satisfy/to fulfill/to act in place of/substitute/sufficient/full

sentences.english: We have abundant oil seeds to sell.
sentences.chinese: 我們有充裕的油籽出售。

sentences.english: There is abundant firewood in the forest.
sentences.chinese: 森林裏有充裕的薪柴可用。

sentences.english: So every person on the earth can enjoy abundance without any scruple.
sentences.chinese: 所以，地球上的每個人都可以毫無顧忌地享受充裕。

sentences.english: The sunny savanna yields no food.
sentences.chinese: 這個陽光充裕的無樹平原不產食物。

sentences.english: Prison life consists of routine. after which more routine.
sentences.chinese: 監獄生活充裕了一段又一段的例行公務。

sentences.english: Captain Alison will set out at eight o'clock so we shall have plenty of time.
sentences.chinese: 艾利森船長將於8點鐘啓航，因此我們有充裕的時間。

sentences.english: He has stocked the shop up very well.
sentences.chinese: 他給商店辦貨辦得很充裕。

sentences.english: The other nearby resource that will be incredibly useful is the good building stone in Sanuki to the north east.
sentences.chinese: 在北部的贊歧東部，充裕的石材資源也頗令人心動。

sentences.english: In an age of planty, we feel spirit hunger.
sentences.chinese: 在物質充裕的年代，我們感覺精神飢渴。

sentences.english: His broad fields and well-filled granaries pass from under his control.
sentences.chinese: 他那廣大的田地和充裕的倉庫不再受他的支配了。

sentences.english: With the sea on three sides, Sanya has abundant maritime resources.
sentences.chinese: 三亞三面環海，有着充裕的海洋資源。

sentences.english: He that willhavehis farm full, must keep an old cock andayoung bull.
sentences.chinese: 若想使農莊充裕，必須有一隻老母雞和一頭嫩牛仔。

sentences.english: Prison life consists of routine which usuficwoulsly more routine.
sentences.chinese: 監獄生活充裕了一段又一段的例行公務。

sentences.english: Public builders, flush with cash, have since re-entered some markets.
sentences.chinese: 公共建築，現金充裕，自重新進入某些市場。

sentences.english: He that will have his farm full,must keep an old cock and a young bull.
sentences.chinese: 想使農莊充裕，就得養一隻老公雞和一頭小公牛。

sentences.english: There are very plentiful light resources and high production potentialities of radiation in Cele of Xinjiang.
sentences.chinese: 策勒光能資源十分充裕，光能生產潛力較大。

definition: to be deficient in sth/to be short of sth (supplies, money etc)
lit. pulling on the lapels exposes the elbows (idiom)/strapped for cash/unable to make ends meet
faultless/complete/perfect/to leave nothing to be desired
